4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, catastrophe savings accounts
6 cover insurance deductibles and other uninsured
7 portions of risks of loss from windstorm events to
8 owners of residential property.
9 This bill would require catastrophe savings
10 accounts to be held in Alabama banks, credit unions, or
11 veterans financial institutions.
12
13
14 A BILL
15 TO BE ENTITLED
16 AN ACT
17
18 Relating to catastrophe savings accounts; to amend
19 Section 40-18-310, as amended by Act 2026-100, 2026 Regular
20 Session, Code of Alabama 1975; to require accounts to be held
21 in Alabama banks, credit unions, or veterans financial
22 institutions.
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
24 Section 1. Section 40-18-310, as amended by Act
25 2026-100, 2026 Regular Session, Code of Alabama 1975, is
26 amended to read as follows:
27 "§40-18-310
28 As used in this article, the following terms shall have
Page 1

As used in this article, the following terms shall have
HB615 INTRODUCED
29 the following meanings:
30 (1) CATASTROPHE SAVINGS ACCOUNT. A regular savings
31 account or money market account, established in a bank or
32 credit union with a brick and mortar location in Alabama or a
33 veteran-related financial institution, by an insurance
34 policyholder who is a state income taxpayer for residential
35 property in this state to cover: (i) an insurance deductible
36 under an insurance policy for one residential property owned
37 by a taxpayer that covers hurricane, rising floodwaters, or
38 other catastrophic windstorm event damage or by an individual
39 to cover self-insured losses for the taxpayer's residential
40 property from a hurricane, rising floodwaters, or other
41 catastrophic windstorm event; (ii) the annual cost of a
42 FORTIFIED endorsement to supplement an insurance policy; or
43 (iii) the cost of mitigation actions that would reduce the
44 risk of hurricane, rising floodwaters, or other catastrophic
45 windstorm event damage, including, but not limited to, costs
46 associated with reroofing and obtaining evaluation services to
47 qualify for a FORTIFIED designation, collectively, "Qualified
48 Catastrophe Expenses." The account must be labeled as a
49 catastrophe savings account in order to qualify as a
50 catastrophe savings account as defined in this article. A
51 taxpayer may establish only one catastrophe savings account
52 and shall specify that the purpose of the account is to cover
53 the Qualified Catastrophe Expenses.
54 (2) WINDSTORM EVENT. Windstorms, cyclones, hurricanes,
55 tornadoes, high winds, and hail, and similar perils not
56 normally among those covered under most property casualty
Page 2

normally among those covered under most property casualty
